to be advanced a little bit.

00:17:33.580 --> 00:17:39.502
But we also felt like if
we took the time to say

00:17:39.502 --> 00:17:41.460
there are 10 times as
many microbes in your gut

00:17:41.460 --> 00:17:43.370
as there are human
cells in your body.

00:17:43.370 --> 00:17:45.330
Which doesn't make
sense, because you

00:17:45.330 --> 00:17:47.260
would think that you'd
be oozing out bacteria,

00:17:47.260 --> 00:17:50.130
but it actually is fine because
bacteria are a lot smaller

00:17:50.130 --> 00:17:51.270
than human cells, right?

00:17:51.270 --> 00:17:53.400
That actually is, like,
two or three seconds

00:17:53.400 --> 00:17:56.400
of very, very
precious time wasted.

00:17:56.400 --> 00:17:58.340
And sort of loses the
momentum of the video.

00:17:58.340 --> 00:18:04.540
So we decided to do an animation
to explain all of that instead.

00:18:04.540 --> 00:18:07.610
